                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-520" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MORRELL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. On the evening of the 6th of July I was called by Boltwood—I received the prisoner into custody, with this shawl—the prisoner first said he had bought the ticket of a man, and then he said he had taken the shawl from his master's shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I met a woman in Shoreditch, who asked me to go and pledge this shawl—She said she did not like to go herself as she owed them some money, and she would give me 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and the ticket.</p>
